The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
		 Monday, May 31, 2004  BRIEFS
				 																																	Krishnagar, May 30: Omnath Prasad, 40, was arrested today from Shyamnagar in North 24-Parganas on the charge of cheating youths by falsely promising them jobs. Dilip Pal of Chakdah, about 60 km from Calcutta, had paid Prasad Rs 50,000 for a job in the railways. When he realised that the claims were false, he informed the police who arrested Prasad.				 																																	Barasat: Mahasveta Devi, writer and social activist, came down heavily on the state government on Sunday for failing to maintain the ecological balance and preserve the wetlands in Bengal. She was speaking at a blood donation camp organised by an NGO at Champadali in Barasat.
